    description:
      'Background & Purpose of the Job<br /><br />Are you looking for an exciting opportunity to be part of a winning team? Unilever is recruiting for a Quality Supervisor to join our \u00ad\u00ad\u00ad\u00ad\u00ad\u00ad\u00ad\u00ad\u00adIndependence Team. The Independence Site is primarily a dry savory operation producing Knorr and Lipton products that also has a Tea production operation.\u00a0 Every day is a new adventure as the site continues to grow and improve. On any given day, two billion people use Unilever products to look good, feel good and get more out of life. With more than 400 brands focused on health and wellbeing, no company touches so many people\u2019s lives in so many ways. Our portfolio ranges from nutritionally balanced foods to indulgent ice creams, affordable soaps, luxurious shampoos and everyday household care products.<br /><br />Who You Are & What You\u2019ll Do<br /><br />Reporting to the site Quality Manager, the Quality Specialist plays a role in ensuring Unilever\u2019s goal to delight consumers. This person upholds factory specifications, standards and Quality Management System (QMS) for food safety, quality assurance and controls in alignment with applicable regulatory requirements. This key Quality role drives site Quality improvement activities to ensure consumer safety & overall product quality and address consumer / customer issues. This includes vendor contract optimization, process capability monitoring, partnering in formulation challenges and updating relevant standards, creating and executing relevant training, cleaning & allergen validations and hygienic design gatekeeping. This person will work with our other Quality Specialists and production teams in identifying and executing process and material improvements. Each Quality Specialist role become a subject matter expert in his/her areas of ownership.\u00a0 These areas of ownership rotate periodically to broaden each individual and create sustainability within the department. This role will report on program performance to the Quality manager.<br /><br />You\u2019re a strategy guru:\u00a0you have a knack for linking tactical activities to program progression plans to sustainably meet or exceed performance targets<br /><br />You\u2019re a dot connector:\u00a0you thrive on problem-solving & getting things done in collaboration with all departments<br /><br />You love to win, and have fun doing it:\u00a0you bring your authentic self to the job and lift others up through your successes<br /><br />You\u2019re a story teller:\u00a0you bring others on the Quality improvement journey. You celebrate the wins and help others learn from the opportunities.<br /><br />You\u2019re a changemaker:\u00a0you drive a step change in Quality by inspiring all levels down to the shop floor<br /><br />You\u2019re a paradox navigator:\u00a0you hold all levels of the organization accountable to be Quality champions<br /><br />What You\u2019ll Need To Succeed<br /><br />Bachelor Degree, preferably in Biology, Food Sciences, Regulatory Sciences, or Chemistry<br />Minimum two years of quality related experience, preferably in a food environment<br />Experience with HACCP Plans, FSMA, and USDA preferred<br />Strong analytical skills; ability to translate data into action and follow-through<br />Excellent math, written and verbal communication skills<br />Team leadership/ supervisory experience is preferred, but not required<br />Computer proficiency, esp. Excel, Word, PowerPoint, EWM, SAP; ability to provide relevant input and deploy/train new digital quality systems<br />Flexible, motivated individual with the ability to adapt quickly and effectively.<br />Ability to lead in a fast-paced and challenging environment<br />Basic knowledge of dry savory composition, sanitation principles, microbiology and quality assurance policies and regulations.<br />Experience with lean manufacturing principles and statistical analytics platforms preferred<br />Applied knowledge of dry food manufacturing equipment and digital systems preferred<br />Must be able to work evening to overnight shift<br /><br />Pay: The pay range for this position is $68,000 to $102,000. Unilever takes into consideration a wide range of factors that are utilized in making compensation decisions including, but not limited to, skill sets, experience and training, licensure and certifications, qualifications and education, and other business and organizational needs.<br /><br />Bonus: This position is bonus eligible.<br />Long-Term Incentive (LTI): This position is LTI eligible.<br /><br />Benefits: Unilever employees are eligible to participate in our benefits plan. Should the employee choose to participate, they can choose from a range of benefits to include, but is not limited to, health insurance (including prescription drug, dental, and vision coverage), retirement savings benefits, life insurance and disability benefits, parental leave, sick leave, paid vacation and holidays, as well as access to numerous voluntary benefits. Any coverages for health insurance and retirement benefits will be in accordance with the terms and conditions of the applicable plans and associated governing plan documents.<br />\u00a0<br /><br />What We Can Offer You<br /><br />Unilever at a Glance |\u00a0Working at Unilever |\u00a0Powering our Purpose |\u00a0Planet & Society |\u00a0Unilever\u2019s Brands |\u00a0Unilever on LinkedIn |\u00a0Strategy | Unilever |\u00a0Diversity, Equity & Inclusion |\u00a0Careers at Unilever |\u00a0 Benefits, Learning, & Wellbeing |\u00a0Latest News About Unilever\u00a0\u00a0<br /><br />------------------------------------<br /><br />Unilever is an organization committed to diversity and inclusion to drive our business results and create a better future every day for our diverse employees, global consumers, partners, and communities. We believe a diverse workforce allows us to match our growth ambitions and drive inclusion across the business. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, national origin, or protected veteran status and will not be discriminated against on the basis of disability.\u00a0<br /><br />Employment is subject to verification of pre-screening tests, which may include drug screening, background check, credit check and DMV check.<br /><br />\u00a0<br /><br />If you are an individual with a disability in need of assistance at any time during our recruitment process, please contact us at NA.Accommodations@unilever.com. Please note: This email is reserved for individuals with disabilities in need of assistance and is not a means of inquiry about positions or application statuses.',
