    description:
      "Commercial Credit Analyst Training Program<br /><br />Country: United States of America<br /><br />POSITION SUMMARY \u2013 CREDIT ANALYST<br /><br />We are looking for future leaders to join Santander\u2019s unique, one year, comprehensive Commercial Credit Training Program. You will start your journey as a Credit Analyst and join other program colleagues for 2 months of intensive classroom training followed by 10 months of rotations. In this role, you will learn critical analytical and communication skills to develop a career with a rapidly growing global financial services firm. Santander Group is one of the top 10 Banks worldwide. The US operation with $155 billion in assets is headquartered in Boston with offices across the United States.<br /><br />The program curriculum is rigorous and provides foundational, technical underwriting skills to prepare you to make an immediate impact on the business. Rotations through our Underwriting & Portfolio Management and Originations teams provide the practical experience working in deal teams on live transactions for real clients across Commercial Banking. The program also includes an array of leadership and development training, a speaker series, mentoring and group community volunteering. Following graduation, analysts are placed within a Commercial Banking Underwriting & Portfolio Management team based upon business line need.<br /><br />The Commercial Banking Credit Analyst Program offers unparalleled exposure to the Executive Leadership Team. Working at Santander you will engage in a high performance culture, with the goal of building lasting loyalty with our clients and developing your career. We seek exceptional candidates with an analytical mindset, intellectual curiosity, communication and teamwork skills ready to play an important role in a collaborative, fast paced deal team environment to help deliver solutions for our clients.<br /><br />SANTANDER BANK<br /><br />Santander Bank US is a subsidiary of Madrid-based Santander Group, the largest retail and commercial bank in the Eurozone and the # 1 financial institution in Latin America. Founded in 1857, with over 200,000 employees and 144 million customers, Santander Group operates in over 40 countries. In the United States Santander\u2019s accelerated growth leverages the firm\u2019s world class global capabilities.<br /><br />COMMERCIAL BANKING <br /><br />Santander\u2019s Commercial Banking Division is an active provider of Capital, Treasury Management, and Risk Management solutions to thousands of middle market and mid-corporate companies across the U.S. In addition, Santander\u2019s significant international presence uniquely positions the Bank to help companies grow their businesses. Commercial Banking has product and industry sector expertise in Technology, Media, Telecommunications, Commercial Real Estate, Asset Based Lending, Cash Flow Lending, Leveraged Finance, Equipment Leasing, Automotive Dealer Finance, Food and Beverage, Healthcare, Education, and Government Banking.<br /><br /><br />JOB REQUIREMENTS & RESPONSIBILITIES<br />Graduation from the Program requires passing all requisite examinations, individual and group assessments during the classroom training, and all continuous education.<br />Credit Analysts will have the following responsibilities:<br />1. Complete the Commercial Credit Training Program curriculum<br />2. Perform credit analysis and underwriting on new deals, renewals/reviews and<br />modifications verifying compliance with credit policy<br />3. Conduct due diligence on clients, industries and markets to identify key<br />business drivers and risks<br />4. Assist in the preparation of valuation and capital structure analysis in<br />conjunction with credit approvals for new and existing clients<br />5. Assist with legal closing process, preparing, reviewing, and validating<br />documentation, ensuring compliance and conditions are met<br />6. Communicate with all deal team members including: origination, underwriting, credit risk management, monitoring, and loan closing<br />7. Monitor and assess client financials, collateral, loan covenants and risk<br />ratings on a periodic basis<br />8. Assess and formally review client risk through periodic Portfolio Reviews,<br />Internal Audits, External Audits, and ad-hoc reviews<br />9. Continuously monitor client financials/information to ensure performance to<br />financial plan and compliance with credit agreement<br />10. Prepare credit approval document and assist deal team in deal screen and<br />approval meetings<br />11. Prepare customer risk rating and financial statement analysis<br /><br /><br />QUALIFICATIONS<br /><br />Education: Bachelor's Degree, minimum 3.5 cumulative GPA preferred<br />Experience: Demonstrated work ethic and proficiency in both academics, internships, extracurricular activities, and relevant leadership positions<br />\u200b<br /><br />REQUIRED SKILLS <br /><br />Strong intellectual curiosity, with the demonstrated ability to ask insightful questions, think critically, problem solve, and probe for deeper understanding<br />Commitment to excellence, exhibits high standards, open to new challenges and learning experiences<br />Strong written and verbal communicator with the ability to offer opinions and share perspective in a professional setting<br />Possesses a strong work ethic, positive attitude, perseverance, resiliency, and management by fact<br />Ability to prioritize, manage and meet tight deadlines<br />Strong attention to detail<br />Ability to collaborate within a team and work independently<br />Proficiency in Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint<br /><br />At Santander, we value and respect differences in our workforce and strive to<br />increase the diversity of our teams. We actively encourage everyone to apply.<br />www.santander.com<br /><br /><br />Disclaimer:<br />The above information on this description has been designed to indicate the general nature and level of work performed by employees within this classification. It is not designed to contain or be interpreted as a comprehensive inventory of all duties, responsibilities, and qualifications required of employees assigned to this job.<br /><br />0:00\u00a0/\u00a01:01",
